metadata.name: At Night. #9
metadata.description:
The sun sets in the sky, and our apartment is bathed in a soft glow.

I am sitting on my couch, watching the lights from the windows of our neighbors' apartments. The rays of light shine through the curtains and illuminate their living rooms, casting shadows on the walls.

The rays of light illuminate the curtains; they cast silhouettes of beauty.

art by Genna, July 2022.
designed with P5.

metadata.name: PolyGarden #45
metadata.description:
Polygons, patterns and flowers are mixtured in my garden. I start with a birdeye view of the garden and its geometric structure. The species diversity and the random stack of rocks, sands, fences and other objects are main structures I want to capture, in an abstract and planar style. 

Moreover, in this project, I also try to explore the representation ability of generative art. I select three elements: shape of entity, layout of palette, and stack of object location. The factors behind these elements are the balance of randomness and structure: the generative art generates the variants from randomness but restricts its chaos with structure (deterministic constraints) to represent the meaningful results. 

Variables:
- 4 layouts
- 6 texture patterns
- 15 color palette
- 3 randomness
- 2 completeness

Please be patient with drawing process.

metadata.name: Several pairs of narrow, curved strips #35
metadata.description:
Several pairs of narrow, curved strips

- Using WEBGL1.0
- Textures/Images: None
- 3D Model data: None
- Library: None
- Vertex Shader: 1
- Fragment Shader: 1


Note:
Keyboard m key: Opens the menu. You can save the resolution and the image.
Keyboard f key: fit the screen.
The minimum resolution is 1600px x1600px, but no upper limit is set. The limit is determined by your machine and browser.

GPU is required because of WebGL.
